# Line-ending discipline (Windows port, M1-T1 / review OV3).
#
# Claude Code installs this plugin by cloning the repo on the user's machine.
# Git for Windows defaults core.autocrlf=true, which would check out *.sh with
# CRLF line endings — and bash dies on the invisible \r before any script runs.
# Pinning eol=lf here protects every future clone regardless of local config.

* text=auto eol=lf
*.sh text eol=lf
*.py text eol=lf
*.md text eol=lf
*.json text eol=lf
*.yml text eol=lf
*.yaml text eol=lf

# Binary assets — never touch line endings
*.png binary
*.jpg binary
*.pdf binary
